==Russian==

===Etymology===
From the French ''[[chanter#French||ne chantera pas]]'', meaning ''does not sing''. The origin of the word '''шантрапа''' goes back to the 18th century when serfhood was still common in Russia. Serfs were divided into two categories, those who were able to sing (''chantera'') and those who could not. The latter were traditionally less educated and were in lesser regard than the former.

===Noun===
'''шантрапа''' (šantrapá) {{mf}}

# [[worthless]] person

